. Caldwell presents the dacha world in all its richness and complexity—a "good life" that draws inspiration from the natural environment in which it is situated.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCountry homeszRussia (Federation). 0aGardeningzRussia (Federation). 0aOrganic livingzRussia (Federation). 0aVacation homeszRussia (Federation). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  achanging landscape.  acultural anthropology.  adacha dwellers.  adacha life.  adachas.  aeconomic landscape.  aethnography.  agardening.  agood life.  aliterary influence.  amodern history.  amodern russia.  anatural environment.  anonfiction.  apostsocialist russia.  arural settings.  arussia.  arussian culture.  arussian history.  arussian life.  arussian politics.  arussian traditions.  asimple life.  asocial cultural.  asummer cottage.  atraditional cottages.  atraditional dwellings.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026285040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094787040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947870423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947870/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY